post_text:
As published in the August 31 USDA Nationwide waivers, School Food Authorities (SFAs) may choose to provide meal service under the Summer Food Service Program (SFSP) through December 31, 2020 (subject to available funding) or continue the National School Lunch Program (NSLP) and School Breakfast Program (SBP).
Rudd Rockford Marble Rock School District is participating in this program until December 31, 2020 or until the funding runs out! Starting with today Sept. 8, 2020 as day 1 for free breakfast and lunch meals to every student in our district. Meals will be provided to all children without charge and are the same for all children regardless of race, color, national origin, sex, age or disability, and there will be no discrimination in the course of the meal service.
Thank you and have a great day!

Tomorrow night our Rockford Warriors host their first home football game vs. Turkey Valley. Kick-off is at 7:00pm. Cost is $5.00 to attend. We‚Äôd like to give you some friendly reminders during this time of COVID for attendance at the event.

*Gate admission is $5.00. We would appreciate exact change to eliminate the exchange of money.
*Concessions will be available.
*Please plan to practice social distancing in the stands. If you aren‚Äôt with your immediate family please wear a face covering.
*All elementary students will be expected to be with their parents and no running around will be allowed. As in the last couple years, no footballs will be allowed either.
*Please respect the ropes/out of bounds markers around the field to keep the players, coaches, and officials safe.

Go Warriors!

Important Message about Prom 2020.

Dear Parents and Students,

The Rudd-Rockford Community School District has received guidance from the Iowa Department of Education that schools will NOT be able to hold a school sponsored Prom during the month of June due to COVID-19. Thus, it is with great regret that I inform you of the the tough decision made to cancel the 2020 RRMR Prom.

If you have any questions, please get a hold of me through email at njohnson@rockford.k12.ia.us.

post_text:
ATTENTION Baseball and Softball Parents:

Parents,

We will be having a meeting for baseball and softball players (grades 8-12) and parents Thursday, May 28th at 5:00pm at the fields. This meeting is very important so we can go over all the new guidance from the Dept. of Ed./ Girls Union/Boys Association as we approach the season. If you as a parent have to work or cannot be present, please make sure an older sibling or grandparent can attend with your athlete. We will also be putting up the windscreens, backstop padding, and batting cages after the meeting on both fields. If there is inclement weather, we will meet on Friday, May 29th. Please practice social distancing while at the fields. Thank you!

post_text: Please join us on Friday at 1:00 for our RRMR Teacher/para/employee parade. We will start in Rockford at 1:00, then head to Marble Rock where we will enter town from the west, and then head to Rudd where we will enter town from the south on Glass Ave. If you live in the country, please head to one of the towns to watch. We will be on each of the towns main streets as well as some other side streets. PLEASE stay in your own yards and wave from your front door, porch, sidewalk, driveway, or from wherever you can. We can't wait to see all of you tomorrow!

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians of RRMR students.

Due to circumstances dealing with COVID-19, the Department of Education is opening the Summer Food Program to Parents/Guardians for their children. Please take note of the following:

*Any child between the ages of 1-18 can be served.
*Meals will consist of 2 meals a day (Breakfast/Lunch).
*Meals will be delivered to Rudd & Marble Rock by school van at approximately 11:00 outside the public libraries.
*Meals can be picked up at the Rockford School. (Please use back high school cafeteria door only from 11:00-11:30.)
*The first delivery/pick up will be Thursday, March 19th.
*Meal deliveries will be available on Monday and Thursday of each week.
If you would like to receive meals please fill out the google form. The form will be open during the duration of COVID-19. You only need to sign up once. Once you sign up you will remain on the list until meals are done being delivered at the end of four weeks.

Please use this link to sign up for meals: https://forms.gle/L5uzPHwgwrQoPLPRA

post_text:
Parents, As you may have heard, the Governor has just recommended schools close for the next four weeks. We understand this is scary and uncertain, to say the least. We will continue to plan and keep you updated as the day goes by tomorrow. We know you have lots of questions.

Beginning tomorrow there will not be school at RRMR for the next four weeks. There will be no SOAR tomorrow either. However, there will be another press conference tomorrow where the Governor could provide childcare guidance for our program.

If you have questions, please reach out. Please be patient as we will do our best to give you the information you need. Some of our planning tomorrow will be how to offer meals, how to deliver personal items that may be needed, etc. Our teachers will also try to reach out to you ASAP. Thank you for your support in helping us keep everyone safe during this trying time.

It is my pleasure to announce that the Rockford athletic department received a generous grant from the Beth E. Reinhart Charitable Trust. This grant will enable all students K-12 at the Rudd-Rockford-Marble Rock CSD to attend regular season athletic events free of charge. For those who already bought activity passes for their children, you will be refunded the full amount. Thank you to the Beth E. Reinhart Charitable Trust for their generous donation to the students of RRMR.

IT IS A GREAT DAY TO BE A WARRIOR!
